com.argox.sdk.barcodeprinter.connection

Interface IPrinterConnection

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FileConnection, PrinterConnection, PrinterDeviceConnection, TCPConnection

    public interface IPrinterConnection
    This interface is the basic interface used as a port.

      • write

        void write(byte[] array,
           int offset,
           int count)
    throws java.io.IOException
        This function is used to write specified byte blocks of the buffer to the connection.
        Parameters:
        array - [in] The data to be written into the connection. Data type: byte array.
        offset - [in] The zero-based byte offset from 'array', used to start copying bytes into the current connection.
        count - [in] Number of bytes to be written into the current connection.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterConnectionException - I/O Error occurred, or connection is not established. System.IO.IOException exception has occurred.
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range. System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException exception has occurred.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - Failed to write data into connection. Non-System.IO.IOException exception has occurred.
        BarcodePrinterWriteTimeoutException - Write data timeout.
        java.io.IOException

      • read

        int read(byte[] array)
  throws java.io.IOException
        This function is used to read the byte blocks from the connection and transferred into the buffer specified. This call is non-blocking.
        Parameters:
        array - [out] This is the buffer in which to place the read byte block. Data type: byte array.
        Returns:
        [out] Return the total number of bytes read into the buffer. If unable to provide the number of bytes as required, the returning number may be smaller than the required number of bytes; if it has reached the end of data stream, then it will be zero.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterConnectionException - I/O Error occurred, or connection is not established. System.IO.IOException exception has occurred.
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range. System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException exception has occurred.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - Failed to read data from the connection. Non-System.IO.IOException exception has occurred.
        BarcodePrinterReadTimeoutException - Read data timeout.
        java.io.IOException
